Albany International Corporation (AIN) Stake Held by Alliancebernstein L.P.

					Posted by Brian Himes on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 



Alliancebernstein L.P. maintained its position in  Albany International Corporation (NYSE:AIN) during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor  owned 40,055 shares of the textile maker’s stock at the end of the first quarter. Alliancebernstein L.P.’s holdings in Albany International Corporation were worth $1,845,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Other hedge funds and other institutional investors also recently bought and sold shares of the company. Thrivent Financial for Lutherans boosted its position in  Albany International Corporation by 5.6% in the fourth quarter. Thrivent Financial for Lutherans now owns 15,490 shares of the textile maker’s stock worth $717,000 after buying an additional 820 shares during the last quarter.  State Street Corp boosted its position in  Albany International Corporation by 7.7% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 627,010 shares of the textile maker’s stock worth $29,034,000 after buying an additional 44,915 shares during the last quarter.  Bbva Compass Bancshares Inc. boosted its position in  Albany International Corporation by 6.7% in the first quarter. Bbva Compass Bancshares Inc. now owns 6,152 shares of the textile maker’s stock worth $283,000 after buying an additional 384 shares during the last quarter.  Alambic Investment Management L.P. boosted its position in  Albany International Corporation by 11.2% in the first quarter. Alambic Investment Management L.P. now owns 27,298 shares of the textile maker’s stock worth $1,257,000 after buying an additional 2,748 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Schaper Benz & Wise Investment Counsel Inc. WI bought a new position in  Albany International Corporation during the first quarter worth approximately $939,000. 86.92% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 


 Get Albany International Corporation alerts:



Shares of Albany International Corporation (AIN) opened at 54.40 on Friday. The stock’s 50 day moving average is $52.39 and its 200 day moving average is $48.09. Albany International Corporation has a 12 month low of $37.00 and a 12 month high of $55.15. The firm has a market cap of $1.75 billion, a PE ratio of 34.89 and a beta of 1.73. 




The company also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Monday, July 10th. Stockholders of record on Wednesday, June 7th were paid a $0.17 dividend. This represents a $0.68 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 1.25%. The ex-dividend date  was Monday, June 5th. Albany International Corporation’s dividend payout ratio  is currently 43.59%. 
