Albany International Corporation (AIN) Rating Increased to Buy at BidaskClub

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 19th, 2017 // No Comments 

BidaskClub upgraded shares of Albany International Corporation (NYSE:AIN) from a hold rating to a buy rating in a research report released on Saturday, July 1st.
Albany International Corporation (AIN) opened at 53.65 on Friday. Albany International Corporation has a 12-month low of $37.00 and a 12-month high of $55.15. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $52.04 and its 200 day moving average is $48.00. The stock has a market capitalization of $1.72 billion, a P/E ratio of 34.41 and a beta of 1.73. 




